@2533 = ~That's good, because I can almost promise you I won't be. But I will try, nonetheless.~
@2534 = ~We do... and you're right.~
@2535 = ~So, no pressure, eh? Well, I'll do my best.~
@2536 = ~I like the sound of that.~
@2537 = ~I don't know if waiting will help. I'll be no more experienced then. But I will wait, if you want to.~
@2538 = ~It's all right, Gavin. I'm sure you'll be fine.~
@2539 = ~Then let's see what we can do about making you more experienced. Starting now.~
@2540 = ~Let's wait. There's no point in rushing now.~
@2541 = ~(With a happy sigh, Gavin cradles your face in his hands and brings your lips to his again. He kisses you deeply, slowly.)~
@2542 = ~(The sounds of the world recede until the only music you hear is your own beating hearts. At last, that too fades to a murmer, and you fall asleep in each others' arms.)~
@2543 = ~Oh...~
@2544 = ~Well, I had considered this as one possible outcome. I had hoped you would say yes, of course, but...~
@2545 = ~Let us continue as we were, then. Maybe a day will come when you feel more able to...~
@2546 = ~What do I expect? I don't know. I hoped you might agree to accept me as your future husband. I feared you might reject me utterly. But I certainly don't know what to expect. What do you mean, exactly?~
@2547 = ~Do you think that after a few easily spoken words and hollow promises, I will accept you as my lover?~
@2548 = ~If I say yes, would you expect me to run away with you to be married this moment?~
@2549 = ~If I say no, will you be heartbroken?~
@2550 = ~If I need more time to decide, will you give it to me?~
@2551 = ~Do you think that commitment excuses you from having to work to keep my affection?~
@2552 = ~I just wanted to know if you had any clear idea what you were getting yourself into, with such a declaration.~
@2553 = ~Your lover? Well, I hoped that one day you might allow it, but when and where would be your choice, if at all.~
@2554 = ~I meant that I wanted to form a bond with you, a promise that we would unite with each other someday in the eyes of our peoples and in the eyes of our gods...~
@2555 = ~And even if those words seemed easily spoken to you, I assure you they were not. I've been agonizing over them for days, and I'm still pretty sure I got it wrong, now that I've seen your reaction.~
@2556 = ~No, of course not. It would be foolish to act so suddenly, without letting it sink in a bit.~
@2557 = ~That would depend on whether you said that you wanted more time to decide or whether you said you wanted nothing further to do with me.~
@2558 = ~If all you need is time, I would give that gladly, but if you reject me completely...~
@2559 = ~Heartbroken is not too strong a word.~
@2560 = ~Yes, of course! I would not want to rush any decision this important.~
@2561 = ~No, I understand that any understanding between two people requires work as well as commitment. I am afraid of neither.~
@2562 = ~I know. I've laid my feelings bare, with no falsehood or deception. I want you for my wife, and I know well the solemnity of that promise.~
@2563 = ~But now, the words are said, and they cannot be taken back, even if I wanted to. You have heard my plea. Will you have me?~
@2564 = ~I will.~
@2565 = ~I'm sorry, Gavin, but I need more time.~
@2566 = ~I would rather leave things as they are, at least for now.~
@2567 = ~Marriage is a big step, Gavin, and not one I am willing to take. Could we not just become lovers?~
@2568 = ~I'm sorry, Gavin. I know you care deeply for me, but I can't return your feelings right now.~
@2569 = ~To be perfectly honest with you, I never thought you would take our flirting so seriously. I'm sorry, Gavin, but I just don't feel for you what you feel for me.~
@2570 = ~Have you? What a revolting thought! And that means no. Not now, not ever.~
@2571 = ~You must be insane.~
@2572 = ~You mean, become lovers with no oath or bond between us? No, <CHARNAME>, I could not. My love for you is built on the hope of a future together, and without that...~
@2573 = ~(sigh) But I know my faults. Without the hope of life together, my love for you would die.~
@2574 = ~But why must it be that way? I cannot commit to you, but I do want you as a lover.~
@2575 = ~No, Gavin, I would not want you to live like that. Hold on to your hope, and one day... Who knows what may happen tomorrow?~
@2576 = ~Gavin, you read too much into our flirtation. It was pleasant for both of us, but I never intended for you to fall in love with me.~
@2577 = ~I can't give you an answer right now. I need to think about it some more.~
@2578 = ~If you rejected me outright, but with kindness, I would keep hoping and praying that one day, your heart would change, and you would accept me. My love for you could survive that.~
@2579 = ~But if you demanded that I allow myself to... lie with you, with no hope, no promise of a future, I would have to accept that you could never care for me.~
@2580 = ~To my shame, I probably would give in to you.... because you are what you are, and if... satisfying your desires helped you defeat the obstacles you face...~
@2581 = ~It would be a great sacrifice, I won't deny it. I would feel used, and a part of me would die in making it. But I would do it, because you must succeed.~
@2582 = ~That is what I want.~
@2583 = ~No, Gavin, I would not ask you to sacrifice your beliefs, even for the sake of my own desires.~
@2584 = ~I don't want that, no. I never asked for your love, and now that you've declared it, I have to reject it. That's all there is to say.~
@2585 = ~You sound like a reluctant martyr being led to the slaughter. It's just an act, Gavin, the simple scratching of an itch. But since you seem to regard it as something deeply spiritual, I won't demand it of you.~
@2586 = ~I'm going to ask you again, because once we're on this course, there is no turning back.~
@2587 = ~If you make me your lover without any vows between us, I will lose respect for you. I do all you ask of me, but never again will I trust you.~
@2588 = ~And if ever you send me from your side, even that will end between us, and I will never be anything more than a friend, even if I do consent to travel with you again.~
@2589 = ~Now I ask you again. Is this really what you want?~
@2590 = ~It is.~
@2591 = ~I don't know if I'm ready for that. Maybe I just need more time to think about commitment.~
@2592 = ~I can't agree to marry you, and I wouldn't ask you to do something you don't want to do for me. Maybe we should just end it, at least for now.~
@2593 = ~So what do we do?~
@2594 = ~Maybe all we need is time. Let's change nothing between us and see how things go.~
@2595 = ~I'm not ready to promise you anything, but I don't want you to do anything you don't want to do. As much as I don't want to, maybe we should end it, at least for now.~
@2596 = ~I don't know.~
@2597 = ~I appreciate that. But it does lead to another question.~
@2598 = ~(sigh) So be it.~
@2599 = ~I'll do as you ask, but not now. The wound is still too fresh.~
@2600 = ~Then let us continue on as we were. There is time enough to decide later.~
@2601 = ~Not what I hoped to hear, but I must accept your choice. Should you change your mind...~
@2602 = ~But no, I will not ask for more than your kindness in rejecting me gently.~
@2603 = ~I... I see. Well, I will not stand between you and...~
@2604 = ~I will not stand in your way.~
@2605 = ~Ouch. That hurt.~
@2606 = ~But you have certainly let me know how you feel about me. I will take it to heart, and find whatever consolation in the totality of your rejection that I may.~
@2607 = ~How could you ever imagine that I could want you?~
@2608 = ~You must know that another holds my heart.~
@2609 = ~It was never more than flirtation between us Gavin. I am sorry you thought it was more.~
@2610 = ~I just can't. Not right now. I thought you knew.~
@2611 = ~How can you expect me to make a decision like that now, with the world falling apart around us?~
@2612 = ~It's just that it's so rushed. I need more time to think.~
@2613 = ~How could you ever doubt my love for you? Of course I'll marry you!~
@2614 = ~Well, I'd better let you get some rest. Sleep well, <CHARNAME>.~
@2615 = ~So sleep well, my love, and dream of sweet things. I will dream of you, and give thanks to Lathander for our love.~
@2616 = ~I've been thinking... maybe it wasn't you.~ [bgav121]
@2617 = ~What?~
@2618 = ~Oh, it was me, all right. Whatever you heard, it's true.~
@2619 = ~Oh, it was me, all right. You were there, you saw.~
@2620 = ~If it wasn't me, who was it?~
@2621 = ~Of course it wasn't me.~
@2622 = ~I was wrong to hold you fully responsible for the wrongness in your soul. I should have been more tolerant, considering the blood you bear.~
@2623 = ~Is that an apology?~
@2624 = ~So that makes you my best friend, does it?~
@2625 = ~The 'wrongness of my soul?' Who are you to say what's right or wrong?~
@2626 = ~So, I can get away with anything, just because I'm a <PRO_RACE>?~
@2627 = ~I don't follow you. You're human, too.~
@2628 = ~Too little, too late, Gavin.~
@2629 = ~You walked away from the hand I offered you once before. I won't give you the chance to do it again.~
@2630 = ~I never really understood it myself, but now that I know what I am, it makes more sense.~
@2631 = ~I'm not saying you did not do what you did. I'm just saying that I was wrong in blaming only you for it.~
@2632 = ~I don't expect you to trust me. Maybe someday, but not now.~
@2633 = ~That's what I'm apologizing for. I was doing just that, by judging you as if you did not...~
@2634 = ~I wasn't talking about the blood you got from your mother.~
@2635 = ~Yet you accepted me into your company not once, but twice. Won't you at least hear me out?~
@2636 = ~Oh, all right. Say your bit, but no promises.~
@2637 = ~Why not? I'm feeling magnaminous today.~
@2638 = ~You're valuable as a healer and a meat shield. Learn your place.~
@2639 = ~I can't explain why I "accepted your company." You're impossible, and yet... I don't know. There's something about you...~
@2640 = ~You're as welcome here as any fit, muscular male would be. You stay as long as I find you easy to look at.~
@2641 = ~I might have accepted you, but that doesn't mean I'm going to keep you. Don't push your luck.~
@2642 = ~I guess you've got about as much to learn about all this as everybody else.~
@2643 = ~You're the <PRO_SONDAUGHTER> of Bhaal. That's a heavy burden to bear, and I can hardly blame you for staggering under the weight of it.~
@2644 = ~You're giving Bhaal credit for more influence in my life than he holds.~
@2645 = ~It's impossible, Gavin. I feel this urge to hurt things, and it never ends.~
@2646 = ~You're making excuses for me, but the truth is that I like who I am. I have no desire to change.~
@2647 = ~I'm more interested in seeing how I do under the weight of *you*.~
@2648 = ~So why do you stay, if you find me so fallible?~
@2649 = ~I had hoped you would not resemble your father so much.~
@2650 = ~<CHARNAME>, I... I had better get to the point.~
@2651 = ~(gulp) <CHARNAME>, I'm afriad you might have the wrong idea about me.~
@2652 = ~Please, Gavin, don't make me ill. I have no desire to bed you. You are easy to look at, however, provided I ignore everything from the neck up.~
@2653 = ~There's something about you that draws me in, even though I know what you are.~
@2654 = ~Are you sure? You might enjoy a tumble.~
@2655 = ~Lathander is the god of athletics and virility, no? How do his priests measure up?~
@2656 = ~And making you blush is such a delight. I do believe I can see the sunrise in your face, just now.~
@2657 = ~I do not tolerate poor performers in my company. I am not saying that I will require your services, but if I do, you will provide them or you will go.~
@2658 = ~Ha! As if! You moron, do you really think I would accept you? But now I know: you think with your balls, even as you mouth pious words.~
@2659 = ~Don't trouble yourself. I'm only looking.~
@2660 = ~I can only hope that you...~
@2661 = ~No. I'll keep that thought to myself. You probably think me a fool already, without sharing the pleas I offer my god on your behalf.~
@2662 = ~This conversation is going nowhere. It would be best if we got back to what we were doing.~
@2663 = ~Ilmater's mercy, <CHARNAME>, if you really are that shallow, you have eyes to see for yourself. It would do you more good, however, to think of the state of your soul.~
@2664 = ~You worry about keeping my body alive and healthy, and leave the worry over my soul to me.~
@2665 = ~My, aren't you moody! One moment, you're contrite over judging me for being a Bhaalspawn, the next, you're berating me for admitting my urges.~
@2666 = ~Can't blame a girl for trying. One of these days, Gavin, I'm going to find out what you keep under your clothing, and you're going to be sorry you held out so long.~
@2667 = ~Gavin, you silly little man, can't you tell when someone is joking?~
@2668 = ~Relax, Gavin. I know how far I can push you.~
@2669 = ~Why do I let myself be baited like this? Never mind.~
@2670 = ~I... <CHARNAME>, do you know what you're asking? I'm Lathander's Dawnbringer. There are things I can't do.~
@2671 = ~Why? Are you mutilated in some way?~
@2672 = ~Then stop wasting my time and get out of my sight.~
@2673 = ~Lathander doesn't have a problem with one person giving another physical pleasure, does he?~
@2674 = ~You're still the same old Gavin, all right. Never mind. Just try to make yourself useful.~
@2675 = ~After everything you have been through, I would not have expected you to do something so childish. Saying suggestive things and then blaming a man for thinking along those suggestions isn't clever, it's juvenile.~
@2676 = ~No, but I can't condone slavery, and you're asking me to become one.~
@2677 = ~Oh, very well. Have it your own way, then.~
@2678 = ~Can't you tell when I'm teasing you?~
@2679 = ~You'll do as you're told or you'll get out of my sight!~
@2680 = ~As you wish. Farewell.~
@2681 = ~When one is unwilling, he does.~
@2682 = ~I'll try, but I'm warning you now that if you push me too far, I will have to leave.~
@2683 = ~Save yourself the trouble. Do it now.~
@2684 = ~I think I know how hard I can push you.~
@2685 = ~If you survive. You are expendable.~
@2686 = ~No, Gavin, don't go. I shouldn't tease you like that, but I just can't seem to stop myself.~
@2687 = ~I hoped things would be different this time, but I see that I was wrong. Farewell.~
@2688 = ~If not, you'll learn.~
@2689 = ~No, I'm not. There is a child in a temple who needs me, if you don't. Farewell.~
@2690 = ~I hope that I'm not. I would hope that you did not consciously decide to become...~
@2691 = ~I know, <CHARNAME>. It must be unbearable. But now that you know, you can resist it. You don't have to be a slave of your blood.~
@2692 = ~That's what I was afraid of. <CHARNAME>... no, I've said enough for now. Let's get back to what we were doing.~
@2693 = ~Quite sure.~
@2694 = ~<CHARNAME>, I begin to think we've about exhausted this conversation, but I have to at least try.~
@2695 = ~You might be the child of Bhaal, but you are also a <PRO_MANWOMAN>. I want to help you. I only hope I can.~
@2696 = ~ I think you finding me in that temple happened for a reason. Maybe...~
@2697 = ~Maybe your soul is reaching out, striving for freedom from the taint of the blood you bear. Maybe I can help you.~
@2698 = ~And here I thought it was just the lure of a nice pair of shoulders.~
@2699 = ~I don't think it's anything that lofty.~
@2700 = ~It's nothing I can explain.~
@2701 = ~I've heard stranger things.~
@2702 = ~It seems too unlikely to be even possible.~
@2703 = ~And then you say something like that, and I wonder how I can stand to be near you.~
@2704 = ~Have you ever stopped to listen to the words that come out of your mouth?~
@2705 = ~I'll try to bear it, but you have to promise you'll try to fight the evil of the blood you bear.~
@2706 = ~Fight it? Why would I want to do that? It's a blessing, not a curse.~
@2707 = ~I can't make any promises, but I'll try.~
@2708 = ~I only wish it was that easy.~
@2709 = ~You have no right to dictate terms to me.~
@2710 = ~(sigh) Never mind.~
@2711 = ~There is always hope, <CHARNAME>, remember that. I want to help you. I only hope you'll let me.~
@2712 = ~I could ask no more.~
@2713 = ~(As promised, Gavin comes to you as you prepare for bed. He wears only shirt and leggings, and looks ill at ease, despite his smile. He embraces you awkwardly, visibly shaking with suppressed emotion.)~ [bg_blank]
@2714 = ~I have come, my love. Do you still want to... lie with me?~
@2715 = ~I have come. Do you still want to... lie with me?~
@2716 = ~I need more time to decide.~
@2717 = ~I'm sorry, Gavin, but I'm not ready yet, after all.~
@2718 = ~Oh, sweet, beloved <CHARNAME>...~
@2719 = ~(Gavin kisses you tenderly, gently stroking your hair. For many moments, he holds you thus, giving you time to get used to his nearness.)~
@2720 = ~I understand, dear one. I will return to my own bedroll, and give you whatever time you need.~
@2721 = ~Sweet <CHARNAME>, do not be sorry. This is important to both of us, and I would not have you rushed into making a decision before you are ready. Come to me again when you are, but for now, I will return to my own bedroll and dream of your cheek against my shoulder.~
@2722 = ~(Gavin kisses you, gently stroking your hair. For many moments, he holds you thus, giving you time to get used to his nearness.)~
@2723 = ~I understand. I will return to my own bedroll.~
@2724 = ~Do not be sorry. I will return to my own bedroll, and we may speak more of this another time, if you wish.~
@2725 = ~(After a time, his kiss becomes more passionate, and you feel his pulse quicken.)~
@2726 = ~(Gavin shivers as your cool fingers slide over his skin. You feel him tense slightly as your fingertips brush a scar beneath his shoulderblade, but he offers no resistance as you explore his torso.)~
@2727 = ~I'm starting to think it might be a mistake to bed each other. Our emotions might lead us to do something rash.~
@2728 = ~(Gavin's breath is a shuddering gasp.) I'm having all I can do to keep myself in check, love, though I will if you want. I'm sorry, but I've wanted this moment for so long, it's hard to control myself. Do you want me to stop?~
@2729 = ~(Gavin's breath is a shuddering gasp.) I'm having all I can do to keep myself in check, but I will. Do you want me to stop?~
@2730 = ~I am sorry. I was carried away by the moment, but if you want to wait, I'll gladly wait.~
@2731 = ~It just feels so rushed. I don't know if I'm ready to discover you that completely quite yet.~
@2732 = ~<CHARNAME>, I... I want to please you, but I don't know how.~
@2733 = ~Maybe this is too much too soon. Our emotions might be out of control.~
@2734 = ~You have to remind me of that now?~
@2735 = ~Relax, Gavin. Your body knows what to do... and if you run out of ideas, I'm sure we can come up with something together.~
@2736 = ~You don't need to be the best lover Faerun has ever known. You just have to mean it.~
@2737 = ~Don't be nervous, Gavin. It won't help.~
@2738 = ~You're right.~
